# Package Manager: pnpm only

Always use `pnpm` — never `npm` or `yarn`.

```bash
# ✅ CORRECT
pnpm install
pnpm add <package>
pnpm remove <package>
pnpm run <script>
pnpm dlx <package>

# ❌ WRONG
npm install
npm run dev
yarn add
npx
```

- Use `pnpm dlx` instead of `npx`
- Use `pnpm add` instead of `npm install <package>`
- Use `pnpm run` instead of `npm run`
